-- Brazil posts primary surplus of 2.13 bln reais in February
-- By Silvio Cascione and Luciana Otoni
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 09:40AM EDT
-- None



BRASILIA, March 28 (Reuters) - Brazil posted a primary budget surplus of 2.13 billion reais ($938 million) in February, the central bank said on Friday.

The primary budget balance, which represents the public sector's excess revenue over expenditures before debt payments, was expected to be a deficit of 500 million reais, according to a median forecast of 16 analysts surveyed by Reuters. The country posted a surplus of 19.9 billion reais in January.